Date: Tue 18 Sep 2001
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: USDA-APHIS, Emergency Management Warning 17: West Nile virus
in
2001, birds in Maine, 18 Sep 2001 [edited
<http://www.aphis.usda.gov/oa/wnv/index.html>

West Nile Virus-positive Birds Reported in Maine
------------------------------------------------
The State of Maine has reported the finding of West Nile virus (WNV)
in 4 dead birds collected in Androscoggin (crow), Cumberland (crow),
Franklin (sharp-shinned hawk), and York Counties (blue jay). The birds
were collected between 22 and 31 Aug 2001.
This is the first-ever detection of WNV in Maine and almost certainly
indicates local transmission of the virus. No human or equine cases of
WNV infection have yet been detected in Maine.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
