Date: Wed 19 Sep 2001 12:42:43 -0400
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: The Charlotte Observer, Tue 18 Sep 2001 [edited

Second West Nile Virus-positive Bird Found in North Carolina
------------------------------------------------------------
Cabarrus County has the Charlotte area's first case of West Nile
virus, but health officials said on Mon 17 Sep 2001 that the
probability of an outbreak of human disease is low. The infected bird
is the second case of West Nile virus infection in North Carolina [in
2001 and more [may be on the way, state experts said.
The diagnosis comes about one year after the state's first case, a
crow discovered near Jordan Lake in Chatham County [in 2000.
State officials have no plans for a wide spray of insecticide in
Cabarrus, since the mosquito season is ending and mosquito
populations are declining.
(Byline Mark Johnson and Gail Smith-Arrants)
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
