West Nile virus-positive Birds in Indiana Now Total 12
----------------------------------------------------------
Seven more dead birds found positive for West Nile virus RNA have been
reported by the Indiana State Department of Health molecular virology
laboratory, bringing the total to 12. The total numbers of positives
per county are now as follows: Floyd 5, Lake 4, Marion 1 and Porter
2.
Thus far, no human cases of West Nile Virus infection have been
reported in Indiana.
--
