<http://www.idph.state.il.us/public/press01/westnile9-17-01.htm>

West Nile Virus-positive Birds Now Total 51
-------------------------------------------
The Illinois Department of Public Health today reported that 12 more
dead crows collected in the Chicago area have preliminarily tested
positive for West Nile virus, bringing to 51 the number of birds that
have either been confirmed or are possible positives since the virus
was first detected in the state on 5 Sep 2001.
No human cases of West Nile disease have been reported in the state of
Illinois.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
