Date: Thu 20 Sep 2001
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Connecticut Department of Health, press release, Wed 19 Sept
2001
[edited
<http://dep.state.ct.us/mosquito/index.asp>.

Additional Isolations of West Nile virus from Birds in Connecticut
------------------------------------------------------------------
The Department of Public Health Laboratory reported today 39
additional birds testing positive for West Nile virus (WNV). The birds
were from: Branford, Bridgeport, Easton, Greenwich, Hartford, New
Britain, Stamford, Stratford, and Trumbull. The birds were found
between 22 Aug and 6 Sep 2001.
This brings the total number of birds that have tested positive for
WNV in Connecticut to 182.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[The most significant of these reports are the first ever detection of
West Nile virus in Maine and the first isolations of West Nile virus
from birds in Kentucky and Tennessee. - Mod.CP
